SIMPLE: doctrine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: doctrine
<hw>doc"trine</hw> <pr>(d⟦ocr⟧k"tr⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>doctrine</ets>, L. <ets>doctrina</ets>, fr. <ets>doctor</ets>. See
<er>Doctor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Teaching;
instruction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He taught them many things by parables, and said unto them in his
<qex>doctrine</qex>, Hearken.</q> <rj><qau> Mark iv. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is taught; what is held, put forth as
true, and supported by a teacher, a school, or a sect; a principle or
position, or the body of principles, in any branch of knowledge; any
tenet or dogma; a principle of faith; <as>as, the <ex>doctrine</ex> of
atoms; the <ex>doctrine</ex> of chances.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>doctrine</xex> of gravitation.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>I.
Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Articles of faith and <qex>doctrine</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>
Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The Monroe doctrine</b></col> <fld>(Politics)</fld>,
<cd>a policy enunciated by President Monroe (Message, Dec. 2, 1823), the
essential feature of which is that the United States will regard as an
unfriendly act any attempt on the part of European powers to extend
their systems on this continent, or any interference to oppress, or in
any manner control the destiny of, governments whose independence had
been acknowledged by the United States.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Precept; tenet; principle; maxim; dogma.</syn>
<usage>-- <er>Doctrine</er>, <er>Precept</er>. <xex>Doctrine</xex>
denotes whatever is recommended as a speculative truth to the belief of
others. <xex>Precept</xex> is a rule down to be obeyed.
<xex>Doctrine</xex> supposes a teacher; <xex>precept</xex> supposes a
superior, with a right to command. The <xex>doctrines</xex> of the
Bible; the <xex>precepts</xex> of our holy religion.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unpracticed he to fawn or seek for power⟦br⟧
By <qex>doctrines</qex> fashioned to the varying hour.</q> <rj><qau>
Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>docudrama</ent>⟦br⟧
